1
00:00:02,710 --> 00:00:04,200
Oh, hey, Joey.

2
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:07,940
- Hey. - Listen, I need to ask you something.

3
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:10,370
You know how my stepdad's in prison?

4
00:00:10,420 --> 00:00:12,320
- Yeah. - Yeah.

5
00:00:12,370 --> 00:00:15,180
He was supposed to get a weekend furlough

6
00:00:15,230 --> 00:00:16,980
so he could go to the wedding.

7
00:00:17,030 --> 00:00:19,310
But he just called and....

8
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:22,200
Well, apparently stabbing lceman in the exercise yard

9
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:24,070
couldn't wait till Monday.

10
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,480
- So he can't come? - No.

11
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,060
And so there's no one

12
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:29,170
to walk me down the aisle.

13
00:00:29,220 --> 00:00:30,260
And....

14
00:00:31,010 --> 00:00:33,320
Well, I would just really love it if you would do it.

15
00:00:34,930 --> 00:00:36,360
- Seriously? - Yeah.

16
00:00:36,410 --> 00:00:39,140
You've, you know, sort of been like a dad to me.

17
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:42,380
I mean, you've always, you know,

18
00:00:42,430 --> 00:00:44,690
looked out for me and shared your wisdom.

19
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:48,910
I am pretty "wisdomous."

20
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:52,850
So, what do you say?

21
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:57,000
Are you kidding? Phoebe, I would be honored.

22
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:59,390
Oh, thank you.

23
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:02,660
I hope....

24
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:06,110
I hope you know how much you mean to me.

25
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:08,590
Listen, I hope....

26
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:11,290
I hope that you know....

27
00:01:14,030 --> 00:01:15,520
I don't want you to see your father cry.

28
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:16,870
Go to your room!

29
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:21,220
《老友记》第十季第十二集 菲比的婚礼

30
00:02:08,930 --> 00:02:11,500
Oh, no, no, no. Let your dad get this.

31
00:02:16,170 --> 00:02:17,450
It's my wedding planner.

32
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,460
She's driving me crazy!

33
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:23,830
Hello? Okay, stop screaming!

34
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,790
Okay, so halibut.

35
00:02:27,570 --> 00:02:28,990
All right, so salmon.

36
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,370
Either way. I don't--

37
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:31,710
It doesn't matter to me.

38
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:33,190
Well, it matters to me!

39
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,970
Well, I don't care. So you pick.

40
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,750
Did you just hang up on me?

41
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:42,160
All right, look,

42
00:02:42,210 --> 00:02:43,420
I need you at the rehearsal dinner

43
00:02:43,470 --> 00:02:45,010
tonight at 1800 hours.

44
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,210
Okay. What time is that?

45
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,380
You don't know military time?

46
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,380
military time:24小时制

47
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:52,550
I must have been in missile training the day

48
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:53,470
they taught that.

49
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:56,540
Just subtract 12.

50
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:59,640
Okay, so 1800 minus 12...

51
00:02:59,690 --> 00:03:01,930
...is 1788.

52
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:03,380
- Six o'clock! - Okay.

53
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,270
Hold on. Yeah? Geller here.

54
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:09,600
No, I said it has to be there by 4:00.

55
00:03:09,650 --> 00:03:10,600
Goodbye.

56
00:03:11,330 --> 00:03:13,530
God. How hard is it to make an ice sculpture?

57
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:15,620
Wait. Ice sculpture? That sounds really fancy.

58
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:17,700
I told you, I just want a simple wedding.

59
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:19,400
Please, honey,

60
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:20,980
leave the details to me.

61
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:21,960
Now, I wanna make this day

62
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:23,630
as special for you as I can.

63
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,750
I was thinking the harpist

64
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,530
should wear white.

65
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:27,340
Harpist?

66
00:03:27,390 --> 00:03:29,630
My friend Marjorie is playing the steel drums.

67
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,140
Oh, she backed out.

68
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:32,590
She did? Why?

69
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,780
I made her.

70
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:37,080
Steel drums don't really say "elegant wedding."

71
00:03:37,130 --> 00:03:39,470
Nor does Marjorie's overwhelming scent.

72
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,260
Hey!

73
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,440
She will shower when Tibet is free.

74
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:55,890
- Hey. You look great. - You too.

75
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:57,810
I'm glad we're having a rehearsal dinner.

76
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:59,680
I rarely practice my meals

77
00:03:59,730 --> 00:04:01,070
before I eat.

78
00:04:02,270 --> 00:04:04,510
What did we say was your one gift to us?

79
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,000
No stupid jokes,

80
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:08,290
but I thought that was for the actual wedding.

81
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:09,530
Rehearse it.

82
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:11,700
Hi.

83
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:13,560
Thanks for coming, you guys.

84
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:14,680
Oh, yeah--

85
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:18,470
I was.... I was going for a handshake.

86
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,470
That why your hand's against my crotch?

87
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:22,010
- That is why. - Yeah.

88
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:25,750
So, Rach, where's Emma?

89
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,900
Monica made me send her to my mom's.

90
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:30,590
Apparently, babies and weddings don't mix.

91
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:33,620
Are you still crying about your damn baby?

92
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:36,860
Pheebs, you got to keep the line moving.

93
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:38,950
Remember, 20 seconds per person.

94
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,950
You see these clowns all the time.

95
00:04:44,690 --> 00:04:46,210
Hey, you're Mike's parents, right?

96
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:47,300
Yes, we are.

97
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:48,950
Our little ones are

98
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,170
growing up fast, aren't they?

99
00:04:52,110 --> 00:04:53,380
- How's that? - You know...

100
00:04:53,430 --> 00:04:55,240
...on one hand, you're happy for them.

101
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:57,740
On the other, it's hard to let go.

102
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,490
Who in God's name are you?

103
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:03,320
I'm not that fond of you either, buddy.

104
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,070
I'm just trying to be nice for the kids.

105
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,620
You know what I realized?

106
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:12,470
We have no idea what we're doing in the wedding tomorrow.

107
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,210
Yeah, I thought we'd be groomsmen.

108
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,870
They would have asked us by now.

109
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,220
When did they ask you to be a bridesmaid?

110
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:20,070
November.

111
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,870
I wanna say it's not looking good.

112
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,360
- Hey, Pheebs? - Sorry?

113
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:26,310
You haven't told these guys

114
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,200
what they're doing in the wedding yet.

115
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:31,250
Well, they're not in the wedding.

116
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,470
What?

117
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:38,560
Well...

118
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,080
...this is really awkward.

119
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,770
Oh, and I can leave.

120
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:46,980
I'm sorry, you guys.

121
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:48,650
But Mike's got his brother

122
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,190
and his friends from school.

123
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,410
So, you know, you were....

124
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:53,290
If it helps,

125
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:54,280
you were next in line.

126
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:56,150
You just missed the cut.

127
00:05:56,650 --> 00:05:58,020
Oh, man.

128
00:05:58,190 --> 00:06:01,220
This is like figure skating team all over again.

129
00:05:58,190 --> 00:06:08,190
figure skating/synchronized swimming/balance beam:均为女子运动项目

130
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,060
I mean, synchronized swimming.

131
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,410
I mean-- I mean, the balance beam.

132
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,490
- Help me. - Football.

133
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,470
Thank you.

134
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:16,650
Oh, Pheebs, spit that out. That has pork in it.

135
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:20,600
I thought the pot stickers were supposed to be vegetarian?

136
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:21,990
Yeah, I changed them.

137
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,680
I sent you a fax about it.

138
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:26,210
I don't have a fax machine.

139
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:29,990
Well, then there are gonna be a few surprises.

140
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:33,660
I can't believe we're gonna be

141
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:36,000
the only people that aren't in this wedding.

142
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:37,860
I know. I hate being left out of things.

143
00:06:37,910 --> 00:06:39,160
And it's a wedding.

144
00:06:39,530 --> 00:06:41,510
It'll be weird if I'm not in it.

145
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,970
- Hey, guys, how's it going? - Fine.

146
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:48,500
We're sitting here, alone, doing nothing.

147
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:50,710
It's our rehearsal for tomorrow.

148
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:54,580
Look, about tomorrow, I've got a question for you.

149
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:56,640
I found out one of my groomsmen had an emergency

150
00:06:56,690 --> 00:06:57,640
and can't make it.

151
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:58,620
What happened?

152
00:06:58,670 --> 00:07:00,120
Who cares? And...?

153
00:07:01,450 --> 00:07:03,630
And I was wondering if one of you guys--

154
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,590
- I'll do it! -No... Me!

155
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:08,070
You both wanna do it?

156
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,650
There's only room for one.

157
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,130
Pick me. I look great in a tux,

158
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,460
and I won't steal focus.

159
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,400
No, Mike.

160
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:16,590
No, no, you wanna pick me. I mean.... Watch.

161
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:24,390
You know, I really don't feel very comfortable

162
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,810
making this decision.

163
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:26,920
You know, Phoebe knows you better.

164
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:28,170
I'm gonna let her choose.

165
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,800
Well, if Phoebe's choosing,

166
00:07:31,850 --> 00:07:34,760
then say hello to Mike's next groomsman.

167
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,500
Oh, I will. But I will need a mirror...

168
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:40,380
...as he is me.

169
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,960
Please. You're going down.

170
00:07:44,010 --> 00:07:45,660
You are going "downer."

171
00:07:45,710 --> 00:07:47,820
They say that on the figure skating team?

172
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,910
I wouldn't know. I didn't make it.

173
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:56,170
You know I'm filling in for Phoebe's stepdad tomorrow,

174
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:56,870
right?

175
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,320
Yeah. Yeah. Hey, thanks for doing that.

176
00:07:58,370 --> 00:08:00,050
Oh, hey, my pleasure.

177
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:02,390
So, what are your intentions with my Phoebe?

178
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:07,470
- I intend to marry her. - Oh, a wiseacre.

179
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,990
I understand you plan to support your wife

180
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,290
by playing the piano?

181
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:16,000
Isn't that kind of unstable?

182
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:19,340
- No more so than acting. - Strike two.

183
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:23,910
You're right. She probably will support me.

184
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,220
Hey, unless we move in with you, Dad.

185
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,080
Strike three.

186
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:32,110
You only get one more, Mike.

187
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,120
So? What did you decide?

188
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,110
I decided to pee.

189
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,670
He didn't tell you?

190
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,920
You have to choose one of us

191
00:08:43,970 --> 00:08:44,780
to be in your wedding.

192
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:46,060
One of the groomsmen fell out.

193
00:08:46,110 --> 00:08:47,190
Oh, no, no.

194
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,200
I can't choose between you two.

195
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:50,840
I love you both so much.

196
00:08:50,890 --> 00:08:52,720
Just not enough to put us in

197
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:54,680
the original wedding party.

198
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:57,150
But I don't wanna choose. It's....

199
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,310
Okay, wait. Rach?

200
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:03,420
Listen, I have a very special bridesmaid task for you to do.

201
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:05,300
Goody! What is it?

202
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:08,120
Well, there's a spot open for only one groomsman...

203
00:09:08,170 --> 00:09:10,230
...and you have to choose between Ross and Chandler.

204
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,400
So good luck with that.

205
00:09:11,970 --> 00:09:12,900
What? What, what, what?

206
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:14,580
No, I don't wanna do that.

207
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:16,400
All right. I guess I have to find a new bridesmaid.

208
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,510
I'll do it!

209
00:09:18,830 --> 00:09:21,090
Okay, it's 2100 hours.

210
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:22,180
Time for your toast.

211
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:24,020
Do I have time to go to the bathroom?

212
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:25,970
You had a bathroom break at 2030.

213
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,850
Pee on your own time, Mike.

214
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,280
In regards to the toasts, okay,

215
00:09:32,330 --> 00:09:33,740
you wanna keep them short.

216
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:35,040
Nothing kills a rehearsal dinner

217
00:09:35,090 --> 00:09:36,860
like long speeches. Okay.

218
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:39,250
You just get in, do your thing, and get out.

219
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,830
Is that what you say to Chandler?

220
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:44,420
It's 2101,

221
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:45,670
and I am not amused.

222
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:48,090
Okay.

223
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:52,050
The bride and groom have a few words they'd like to say.

224
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,680
Okay. Hello, everyone.

225
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,120
And thank you all for being here tonight.

226
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:01,120
So tomorrow's the big event.

227
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,630
Some of you might not know,

228
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:05,520
but Mike and I didn't get off to the best start.

229
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:09,180
Yeah. My friend Joey and l...

230
00:10:09,230 --> 00:10:13,530
...decided to fix each other up with friends. So l--

231
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,580
Oh, okay. I....

232
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:19,850
I gave it a lot of thought,

233
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:22,100
and I fixed him up with my friend Mary Ellen...

234
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:25,350
...who couldn't be here tonight, because.... It's not--

235
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:28,070
It's not important. Well, she's in rehab.

236
00:10:28,950 --> 00:10:29,900
Anyway.

237
00:10:29,950 --> 00:10:33,580
So Joey said that he was fixing me up with his friend Mike...

238
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:35,260
...only he didn't have a friend Mike,

239
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:37,380
so he just brought my Mike.

240
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,370
And-- And--

241
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:43,560
But despite, you know-- It got good.

242
00:10:45,110 --> 00:10:46,700
Ok, I wanna take a moment

243
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:47,890
to mention my mother,

244
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:49,020
who couldn't be here.

245
00:10:49,070 --> 00:10:50,260
Oh, God.

246
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:53,020
And.... And moment's over.

247
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:56,160
So okay.... Oh, no, forget that.

248
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:58,740
I can forget that. Oh, this is funny.

249
00:10:58,790 --> 00:11:02,540
Oh, but you need to know that to get that.

250
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:05,010
So.... Oh, well, okay.

251
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,630
I.... Okay.

252
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:10,620
Okay, Monica, I can't do it like this!

253
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:14,110
This is my wedding, okay?

254
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,950
I don't want this--

255
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,510
Or this-- Or this--

256
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,870
Okay? I just wanted a simple wedding...

257
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,690
...where my fiance can go to the bathroom

258
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:24,270
any time he wants!

259
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:30,070
- You know what? You're done. - What?

260
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,430
You're fired!

261
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,480
Cheers.

262
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,780
- Hey. - Happy wedding day.

263
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:48,510
Happy my wedding day to you.

264
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:50,860
Joey, listen,

265
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:52,140
this is gonna be bridesmaid central,

266
00:11:52,190 --> 00:11:52,700
all right?

267
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:53,840
We're gonna have hair and makeup

268
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:54,950
in the bathroom.

269
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,860
I had to move a couple things in the fridge

270
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:58,450
to make room for the corsages.

271
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,870
因为瑞秋说要把corsage放到冰箱里  乔伊以为可以吃

272
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,870
Man! I wouldn't have had breakfast

273
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,930
if I knew there was gonna be corsages.

274
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:07,480
Hi.

275
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:10,800
About last night....

276
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:14,230
I know you're under a lot of stress, and....

277
00:12:14,390 --> 00:12:17,640
Well, even though the things you said

278
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,440
...as someone who's never been fired before--

279
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,090
My point is....

280
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:24,780
Well, I'm willing to take my job back.

281
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:27,680
Oh, well, that's okay.

282
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:31,020
I think you and I will do much better

283
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:33,160
if you're just here as a bridesmaid.

284
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,630
Is that so?

285
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:38,500
Okay.

286
00:12:38,930 --> 00:12:40,090
If that's really what you want,

287
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:41,160
then here.

288
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,860
I give you the headset.

289
00:12:42,910 --> 00:12:44,760
I don't really wanna give you the headset.

290
00:12:46,050 --> 00:12:47,290
I guess if you're taking over,

291
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:50,430
then you should probably return these messages.

292
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,960
Wow. This is a lot.

293
00:12:52,850 --> 00:12:54,490
But I'm sure you can handle this.

294
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:55,860
I have won awards...

295
00:12:55,910 --> 00:12:57,510
...for my organizational skills.

296
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:58,970
But I'm sure you'll do fine.

297
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,290
You've won awards?

298
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:02,370
I printed them out on my computer.

299
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:05,980
- Hey. - Hi.

300
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:07,160
Where's Rach?

301
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:08,390
She's in her room. Why?

302
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,400
I have to talk to her about

303
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:10,850
this groomsman situation.

304
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,750
Ok, I'm not gonna watch Chandler up there

305
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,810
while I'm in the seats like some chump.

306
00:13:19,850 --> 00:13:22,970
My God, you're breathtaking.

307
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:26,890
What do you want?

308
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:29,270
You haven't by any chance

309
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,550
chosen a groomsman yet, have you?

310
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,380
Ross,

311
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:34,480
please don't make this harder than it already is.

312
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:35,440
I'm not.

313
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:37,480
I'm making it easier. Pick me.

314
00:13:38,590 --> 00:13:40,710
Chandler said it's important to him too.

315
00:13:40,710 --> 00:13:42,150
Listen. Listen.

316
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:43,590
Whoever you pick

317
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,580
is gonna walk down the aisle with you.

318
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,430
Now, I promise I won't say a word.

319
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,800
But if you pick Chandler...

320
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:51,310
...he's gonna be whispering stupid jokes

321
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,830
in your ear the whole time.

322
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:56,180
Oh, you are the lesser of two evils.

323
00:13:56,180 --> 00:13:57,380
Yes!

324
00:14:03,370 --> 00:14:05,460
Sven, I don't understand what you're saying.

325
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,330
What is wrong with the flowers?

326
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,840
"Lorkins"? What the hell are "lorkins"?

327
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:10,960
I know.

328
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,420
Hey.

329
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:15,010
Mike, if you were Swedish...

330
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:18,280
...and you were saying the word "lorkins," what flower would that be?

331
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:20,040
Orchids?

332
00:14:20,090 --> 00:14:20,760
Right there!

333
00:14:20,810 --> 00:14:22,700
That's why I'm marrying you.

334
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,740
Hello, Michael.

335
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:34,200
Joseph.

336
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,880
May I have a word with you, please?

337
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:50,110
This is...

338
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,020
...great.

339
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:54,270
Have a seat.

340
00:14:57,670 --> 00:14:59,130
Last night...

341
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,840
...l tried to welcome you into my family.

342
00:15:05,970 --> 00:15:09,220
And instead, you disrespect me.

343
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,420
I cannot allow this.

344
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:15,570
Are you rehearsing for some really bad Mafia movie?

345
00:15:16,710 --> 00:15:18,310
More back talk.

346
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,200
And yes,

347
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:22,150
I may be borrowing a few lines

348
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,720
from my recent unsuccessful audition...

349
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:26,160
...for <i>Family Honor 2:</i>

350
00:15:26,210 --> 00:15:27,930
<i>This A-Time It's A-Personal.</i>

351
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,800
Joey, I kind of have a lot to do today.

352
00:15:32,850 --> 00:15:33,610
What do you want?

353
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:35,480
I want you to take this seriously!

354
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:37,020
Phoebe is very,

355
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,340
very important to me, okay?

356
00:15:39,390 --> 00:15:40,160
I wanna make sure

357
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:41,490
you are gonna take care of her.

358
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,490
Joe, I love Phoebe.

359
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:48,150
She's the most important thing in my life.

360
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,500
I'd die before I let anything happen to her.

361
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:55,360
That's what I wanted to hear.

362
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,970
Because she's family, okay?

363
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:00,710
And now you're gonna be family.

364
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,640
And there's nothing more important

365
00:16:02,690 --> 00:16:05,430
in the whole world than family.

366
00:16:06,610 --> 00:16:08,520
That must have been one lousy movie.

367
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:10,100
That was me!

368
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:14,850
Hi.

369
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,330
Let's talk about this groomsman thing.

370
00:16:16,380 --> 00:16:17,640
If you pick Ross,

371
00:16:17,690 --> 00:16:19,670
he'll walk you down the aisle just fine.

372
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,400
But if you choose me...

373
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:23,810
...you'll be getting some comedy.

374
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:28,550
Even so...

375
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,000
...l think I'm gonna pick Ross.

376
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,230
Let me tell you why you need to pick me.

377
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:40,040
See, when I was a kid, you know,

378
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:42,770
I was always left out of everything...

379
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:46,440
You know... and it really made me feel insecure.

380
00:16:46,490 --> 00:16:50,330
I was always picked last in gym...

381
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:52,810
...even behind that fat exchange student

382
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:55,040
who didn't know the rules to baseball.

383
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,740
I mean, this guy would strike out

384
00:16:56,740 --> 00:16:58,410
and then run to third.

385
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:02,970
Anyway, if I'm the only one

386
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:04,140
left out of this wedding...

387
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,660
...l just know that all those feelings

388
00:17:05,660 --> 00:17:08,000
are gonna come rushing back.

389
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:12,570
All right, fine, I pick you.

390
00:17:12,620 --> 00:17:13,860
Yes!

391
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:18,190
Make "groom" for Chandler.

392
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:18,190
groom与room谐音 钱德勒做了"伴郎"亦即有了"一席之地"

393
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,360
Oh, my.

394
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:27,460
No, we're gonna do it my way.

395
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:29,700
Because your way is stupid.

396
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,330
All right, I got to go.

397
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,000
I have another call, Reverend.

398
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,010
Hello?

399
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,960
I'm glad we had this little talk.

400
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:38,690
Yes.

401
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:41,460
And thanks for all the wedding night advice.

402
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,080
That didn't make me uncomfortable at all.

403
00:17:44,820 --> 00:17:47,050
All right, so I'll see everybody tonight.

404
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:48,530
- Okay. - Bye.

405
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:53,990
Did you guys know that

406
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,470
there's a giant ice sculpture in the hall?

407
00:17:56,820 --> 00:17:59,060
Oh, my God, what's it doing here?

408
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:01,060
I guess it got sent to the billing address

409
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:02,920
as opposed to the shipping address.

410
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,510
What a pickle.

411
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:07,710
Oh, my God, everything's such a mess.

412
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,810
Why is this happening to me?

413
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:13,240
How bad do you wanna stick your tongue on that?

414
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:22,630
- How's it going? - Good.

415
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:24,840
I'm just getting some coffee

416
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:27,070
so I'm alert for the wedding.

417
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:30,390
That's what I was doing too.

418
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:34,050
Well, you have fun tonight.

419
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,310
- You too. - Oh, I will.

420
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,500
Me too.

421
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:43,580
Wait a minute.

422
00:18:43,630 --> 00:18:45,370
I know why I'm being such an ass.

423
00:18:45,420 --> 00:18:46,450
Why are you?

424
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:49,220
I'm not supposed to tell you.

425
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:50,960
I'm not supposed to tell you.

426
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:53,920
You told us both we could be in the wedding?

427
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,050
In my defense,

428
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,190
you weren't supposed to tell each other!

429
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,850
Rachel, only one of us can do it.

430
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:02,890
You have to choose.

431
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:05,440
You and me together again.

432
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:07,720
Rach, Rach?

433
00:19:07,770 --> 00:19:08,710
Knock-knock.

434
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,070
- Who's there? - I'll tell you at the wedding.

435
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:13,730
Hey, I forgot my scarf.

436
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,490
You know what. I can't do this.

437
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:17,450
I don't know which one of you guys to pick.

438
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,700
Oh, you haven't picked yet?

439
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:20,590
Oh, good, because I had an idea.

440
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,920
I thought it would be fun

441
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:25,010
if the third groomsman was my family dog, Chappy.

442
00:19:25,670 --> 00:19:26,910
What? A dog?

443
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,180
No. Rachel gets to choose.

444
00:19:29,990 --> 00:19:32,140
Wow, this is a tough one.

445
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,850
I think I'm gonna have to go with the dog.

446
00:19:36,090 --> 00:19:37,960
So, what you're saying is that

447
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,120
the chef is at the Hamilton Club...

448
00:19:40,170 --> 00:19:41,290
...but the food is not?

449
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:42,570
And the drinks are there

450
00:19:42,620 --> 00:19:44,340
but the bartender is not?

451
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:47,090
Are you freaking kidding me?

452
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:49,500
How's it going?

453
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,960
- Help me. - What?

454
00:19:52,010 --> 00:19:54,540
I want you to be crazy bitch again.

455
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:58,220
Really?

456
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:00,510
Please?

457
00:20:01,490 --> 00:20:03,340
You really want me to come back?

458
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:05,390
More than I wanna get married.

459
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,620
Okay, people, we are back in business!

460
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:14,480
Oh, God, I have missed you so much. Okay.

461
00:20:14,530 --> 00:20:16,710
Ok. Get your hair and makeup done.

462
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,190
I'll take care of everything.

463
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,860
Hey, what are you guys gonna do?

464
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:20,710
About what?

465
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:23,370
The blizzard. I just saw on the news...

466
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:25,270
...it's the worst snowstorm in 20 years.

467
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:27,520
They already closed all the bridges and tunnels.

468
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:30,580
But the band and the photographer

469
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:32,530
are coming in from New Jersey.

470
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:33,960
I don't think they are.

471
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,340
Looks like you're not gonna

472
00:20:36,390 --> 00:20:37,960
be in the wedding, either.

473
00:20:39,830 --> 00:20:41,380
So sorry, Pheebs.

474
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,370
Well, the club lost its power.

475
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:57,570
Yeah according to the news, most of the city did.

476
00:20:57,620 --> 00:20:59,450
Since when do you watch the news?

477
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,950
For your information...

478
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,590
...since they hired a very hot weather girl.

479
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,270
I can't believe

480
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,030
you aren't getting married today.

481
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:08,950
I know.

482
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,200
Wow, you know, it's so beautiful out there.

483
00:21:12,250 --> 00:21:14,070
You always wanted to get married outside.

484
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,860
Why don't you just do it on the street?

485
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:16,770
What?

486
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:19,190
Well, look, it's hardly snowing anymore.

487
00:21:19,630 --> 00:21:22,960
I mean, you couldn't ask for a more romantic setting.

488
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:24,280
This could be the simple wedding

489
00:21:24,330 --> 00:21:25,760
you've always wanted.

490
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,090
What do you think?

491
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,120
I think I wanna get married to you today.

492
00:21:34,420 --> 00:21:37,790
Me too. Monica, do you think we could do it?

493
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:41,260
Affirmative!

494
00:21:49,190 --> 00:21:51,620
Okay, let's get these chairs out here!

495
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:54,070
Gunther, hit the Christmas lights.

496
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:04,370
Okay, who left the ice sculpture

497
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,210
on the steam grate?

498
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:09,010
Michael.

499
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:11,930
Hey, you made it. Great. Chappy!

500
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:15,270
- There you go. - Hi. Hi.

501
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:17,760
Mom, I know getting married in the street isn't

502
00:22:17,810 --> 00:22:19,060
what you approve of.

503
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:20,760
No, it's lovely.

504
00:22:20,810 --> 00:22:22,770
The lights and the snow.

505
00:22:22,820 --> 00:22:24,700
I could look at them forever.

506
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:26,980
I crushed a pill and put it in her drink.

507
00:22:27,990 --> 00:22:29,730
Come on, sweetheart.

508
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:33,060
You know, Chappy's too small

509
00:22:33,110 --> 00:22:34,430
to handle all this snow.

510
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:36,370
Someone has to walk him down the aisle.

511
00:22:36,420 --> 00:22:38,230
Would this person be in the wedding?

512
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:38,990
I guess.

513
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,250
- I'll do it! - I'll do it!

514
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,330
Chandler, hello?

515
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:44,570
I mean, aren't you scared of dogs?

516
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:45,830
I'm not scared.

517
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:47,630
I'll just take little Chappy and--

518
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,580
He can sense my fear!

519
00:22:48,630 --> 00:22:49,850
My throat is exposed!

520
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:54,700
I guess I'm in the wedding then.

521
00:22:56,150 --> 00:22:57,670
He stinks.

522
00:22:58,670 --> 00:22:59,750
Level one alert!

523
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,270
I repeat, level one, this is not a drill!

524
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:03,710
We have a situation.

525
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:04,500
The minister called.

526
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:05,860
He's snowed in, he can't make it.

527
00:23:05,910 --> 00:23:07,780
- Oh, no. - Hey, don't worry.

528
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,570
I'm still ordained from your wedding.

529
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:10,310
Really?

530
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,240
Yeah. You think I'd give up being a minister

531
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:14,190
and pay to ride the subway?

532
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:17,910
Ministers don't ride the subway for free.

533
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,560
I had to read the Bible pretty carefully,

534
00:23:19,610 --> 00:23:21,450
but, yeah, we do.

535
00:23:22,290 --> 00:23:23,900
Ok, if Joey does the ceremony,

536
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:25,750
then we have to find someone else to walk Phoebe down the aisle.

537
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,910
I'll do it!

538
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:33,930
Okay, Mike and Joey, get in position.

539
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,440
Chandler, come with me.

540
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:44,480
Okay, Joey's doing the ceremony,

541
00:23:44,530 --> 00:23:46,080
and Chandler's giving you away.

542
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:48,910
Oh, okay. Hi, new Dad.

543
00:23:50,850 --> 00:23:53,650
So you ready to do this?

544
00:23:54,430 --> 00:23:56,640
Oh, my God. This is really happening.

545
00:23:57,300 --> 00:24:00,290
